#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.nanvar.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.nanvar"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:1 of
msgid "Compute the variance along the specified axis, while ignoring NaNs."
msgstr "沿指定轴计算方差，同时忽略 NaN。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:3 of
msgid ""
"Returns the variance of the tensor elements, a measure of the spread of a"
" distribution.  The variance is computed for the flattened tensor by "
"default, otherwise over the specified axis."
msgstr ""
"返回张量元素的方差，用于衡量分布的离散程度。默认情况下，方差是针对展平后"
"的张量计算的，否则就在指定轴上进行计算。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:7 of
msgid ""
"For all-NaN slices or slices with zero degrees of freedom, NaN is "
"returned and a `RuntimeWarning` is raised."
msgstr ""
"对于全为 NaN 的切片或自由度为零的切片，将返回 NaN 并引发 `RuntimeWarning`"
"。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:10 of
msgid ""
"Tensor containing numbers whose variance is desired.  If `a` is not a "
"tensor, a conversion is attempted."
msgstr "包含所需方差数值的张量。如果 `a` 不是一个张量，则会尝试进行转换。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:13 of
msgid ""
"Axis along which the variance is computed.  The default is to compute the"
" variance of the flattened array."
msgstr "计算方差所沿用的轴。默认情况下，是计算展平后数组的方差。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:16 of
msgid ""
"Type to use in computing the variance.  For tensors of integer type the "
"default is `float32`; for tensors of float types it is the same as the "
"tensor type."
msgstr ""
"用于计算方差的数据类型。对于整数类型的张量，默认为 `float32`；对于浮点"
"类型的张量，则与张量类型相同。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:20 of
msgid ""
"Alternate output tensor in which to place the result.  It must have the "
"same shape as the expected output, but the type is cast if necessary."
msgstr ""
"用于放置结果的替代输出张量。它必须与期望输出具有相同的形状，如有必要，"
"类型会被转换。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:24 of
msgid ""
"\"Delta Degrees of Freedom\": the divisor used in the calculation is ``N "
"- ddof``, where ``N`` represents the number of non-NaN elements. By "
"default `ddof` is zero."
msgstr ""
"“Delta 自由度”：计算中使用的除数是 ``N - ddof``，其中 ``N`` 表示非 NaN "
"元素的数量。默认情况下，`ddof` 为零。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:28 of
msgid ""
"If this is set to True, the axes which are reduced are left in the result"
" as dimensions with size one. With this option, the result will broadcast"
" correctly against the original `a`."
msgstr ""
"如果设置为 True，则在结果中保留被规约的轴，其大小为 1。使用此选项时，结果"
"将能正确地与原始 `a` 进行广播。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:33 of
msgid ""
"**variance** -- If `out` is None, return a new tensor containing the "
"variance, otherwise return a reference to the output tensor. If ddof is "
">= the number of non-NaN elements in a slice or the slice contains only "
"NaNs, then the result for that slice is NaN."
msgstr ""
"**方差** —— 如果 `out` 为 None，则返回一个包含方差的新张量；否则返回对"
"输出张量的引用。如果 ddof >= 切片中的非 NaN 元素数量，或者切片只包含 NaN"
"，则该切片的结果为 NaN。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:41 of
msgid ":py:obj:`std`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:42 of
msgid "Standard deviation"
msgstr "标准差"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:44 of
msgid ":py:obj:`mean`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:45 of
msgid "Average"
msgstr "平均值"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:47 of
msgid ":py:obj:`var`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:48 of
msgid "Variance while not ignoring NaNs"
msgstr "不忽略 NaN 时的方差"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:50 of
msgid ":py:obj:`nanstd`, :py:obj:`nanmean`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:53 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:54 of
msgid ""
"The variance is the average of the squared deviations from the mean, "
"i.e.,  ``var = mean(abs(x - x.mean())**2)``."
msgstr "方差是与均值的平方偏差的平均值，即 ``var = mean(abs(x - x.mean())**2)``。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:57 of
msgid ""
"The mean is normally calculated as ``x.sum() / N``, where ``N = len(x)``."
" If, however, `ddof` is specified, the divisor ``N - ddof`` is used "
"instead.  In standard statistical practice, ``ddof=1`` provides an "
"unbiased estimator of the variance of a hypothetical infinite population."
"  ``ddof=0`` provides a maximum likelihood estimate of the variance for "
"normally distributed variables."
msgstr ""
"通常均值是按 ``x.sum() / N`` 来计算的，其中 ``N = len(x)``。但如果指定了 "
"`ddof`，则使用除数 ``N - ddof``。在标准统计实践中，``ddof=1`` 提供了假设"
"无限总体方差的无偏估计；而 ``ddof=0`` 则为正态分布变量的方差提供了最大"
"似然估计。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:64 of
msgid ""
"Note that for complex numbers, the absolute value is taken before "
"squaring, so that the result is always real and nonnegative."
msgstr "请注意，对于复数，在平方之前先取绝对值，因此结果始终为实数且非负。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:67 of
msgid ""
"For floating-point input, the variance is computed using the same "
"precision the input has.  Depending on the input data, this can cause the"
" results to be inaccurate, especially for `float32` (see example below)."
"  Specifying a higher-accuracy accumulator using the ``dtype`` keyword "
"can alleviate this issue."
msgstr ""
"对于浮点数输入，方差是以输入数据相同的精度进行计算的。根据输入数据的不同"
"，这可能导致结果不准确，尤其是对于 `float32`（参见下面的示例）。通过使用 "
"``dtype`` 关键字指定更高精度的累加器可以缓解这一问题。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanvar.nanvar:73 of
msgid ""
"For this function to work on sub-classes of Tensor, they must define "
"`sum` with the kwarg `keepdims`"
msgstr ""
"为了让此函数能在 Tensor 的子类上正常工作，它们必须定义带有关键字参数 `"
"keepdims` 的 `sum` 方法。"

